  "prompt": "How do bottle caps work in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In \"Pok\u00e9mon Sun\" and \"Pok\u00e9mon Moon,\" Bottle Caps are items used in the process known as Hyper Training. Hyper Training allows players to maximize the IVs (Individual Values) of their Pok\u00e9mon, which can greatly improve their battle performance.\n\nHere's a brief rundown on how they work:\n\n1. **Obtaining Bottle Caps**: There are several ways to acquire Bottle Caps, including through events, as rewards in certain battles or tournaments, from NPCs, or purchasing in special shops like Festival Plaza.\n\n2. **Hyper Training Location**: You can perform Hyper Training in the Alola region at the Hau'oli City Shopping Mall. Look for Mr. Hyper, an NPC character.\n\n3. **Requirements**: To undergo Hyper Training, your Pok\u00e9mon must be at level 100. You also need at least one Bottle Cap for each stat you want to maximize.\n\n4. **Usage**: Speak with Mr. Hyper when your level 100 Pok\u00e9mon is ready. Select the Pok\u00e9mon and choose which Bottle Cap(s) you wish to use. Each Bottle Cap can be applied to one stat (HP, Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, or Speed) to maximize its IVs to 31.\n\n5. **Effect**: Once a Bottle Cap is used, the chosen stat(s)' IVs are set to 31, the highest possible value, thereby improving the Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s performance in battles.\n\nBy using Bottle Caps wisely, players can ensure their Pok\u00e9mon are at their strongest, which is especially valuable for competitive battling.",
